body:
This example gives a `Broken link in node` error:

``` SystemVerilog
//! verilator --debug-check --lint-only test.sv
class ClsParam #(int A = 0);
    typedef enum int {
        EN_A = A + 0
    } enums_t;
    int val = EN_A;
endclass;

module t;
    ClsParam#(100) cls;
endmodule
```

The reason is the `m_classOrPackagep` field of `AstEnumItemRef` is not relinked after cloning in V3Param, so it's still pointing to the old node. Although the referenced value is still correct, but it affects reference counter in V3Dead and might cause further problems.
